  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Executive (Marine Underwriting & BD)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br /><br />1. Business Development Support</p><ul><li>Assist in preparing quotations, proposals and presentations for marine cargo insurance products. </li><li>Coordinate with brokers and clients to gather necessary information for underwriting. </li><li>Maintain and update client and prospect databases. </li><li>Support marketing initiatives and campaigns to promote marine cargo insurance solutions. </li></ul><p>2. Policy Processing & Administration</p><ul><li>Handle issuance of marine cargo insurance policies, endorsements and certificates.</li><li>Ensure compliance with company guidelines and regulatory requirements. </li><li>Monitor and follow up on pending documentations. </li></ul><p>3. Carry out duties assigned by management.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree holders in Insurance, Maritime Studies or related discipline.</li><li>Preferably with minimum 5 year working experience.</li><li>Prepare to take up Certificate In General Insurance (CGI) exam if required.</li><li>Good working knowledge of Microsoft Office application. </li><li>Possess good interpersonal and communications skills. </li><li>Able to multi-task, is a team player, conscientious, tactful, customer-focused and willingness to learn new skills.</li></ul>",
